newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-SFE wheat nears low in wary market.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-SFE wheat nears low in wary market.

text.p: Option trades again outnumbered futures volume in quiet Sydney Futures Exchange trading on Friday as potential players waited for the market to bottom.
One January 1997 futures trade took place at A$190.00 a tonne, down 50 cents on the trade. Four A$205.00 January call options traded at a A$6.00 premium.
Overnight, Australian wheat was more active with ANZ McCaughan Futures Ltd trading 13 January futures at A$190.00.
"We're just trying to find exactly where the low is at the moment," Brendon Hillary of ANZ McCaughan said.
"I'd say Chicago (is) getting pretty close to a low," he said.
But sellers were not comfortable to unload quantity at present levels. Once confirmation came that the low was in place there would be more confidence, he said.
"Normally speaking we'd expect a run to the upside here," he said.
If Chicago broke out of its range to fall below US$4.50 a bushel the Australian market could fall to around the A$185.00 from its present A$190.00, he said.
